race.comment: LINDERMANN (1) ran his rivals into the ground from the outside draw when a slick winner over 1900m in the G2 Hill Stakes at Rosehill. Expecting more pressure here, and the bulk of these will need to go to new peaks to turn the tables. MILITARIZE (4) convinced he's got a good win in him this preparation after flashing late when fifth in the G2 Hill Stks. Would like to see him race a touch closer here and get into the race on the turn. Respect. EL CASTELLO (7) three runs back for the Pride yard have been okay and worth noting his last win came on this day last year in the Group 1 Spring Champion. On the quick back-up and will hold a forward position. KOVALICA (3) looks the best of the rest fourth-up.
